[Liew Chin Tong](https://liewchintong.com/2020/10/21/1990-the-election-year-that-changed-malaysia/), a DAP politician, posits that 1990 was a watershed year in Malaysian politics as it was the beginning of a nearly three-decade long period of Barisan Nasional (BN) and UMNO dominance, largely led by Mahathir Mohamad. [Strong patriarchal and patronage systems](https://eastasiaforum.org/2019/05/08/patronage-based-business-as-usual-in-new-malaysia/) culminated in Mahathir Mohamad's re-election as the world's oldest Prime Minister in 2018. 

The post-1990 election period was one dominated by incumbents and long-tenured politicians, with lower participation from newer political candidates. 

Since 1990, 10 politicians have won 8 federal or state elections, including including Ku Li, who has won 12 federal and 1 state election in his career). 

